Note:
PowerShell Parser - AST construction for PowerShell scripts

This file provides complete syntax analysis for PowerShell scripts.
Constructs an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) representing the script structure.

Features:
- Complete PowerShell grammar support
- Commands and pipelines
- Control structures (if, while, for, foreach, switch)
- Function and filter definitions
- Variable assignments and references
- Object-oriented features (classes, methods)
- Parameter declarations
- Try-catch-finally blocks
- Cmdlet invocations with parameters
- Array and hashtable literals
- Subexpressions and operators

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- frontends/powershell/powershell_lexer.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/powershell/powershell_lexer.runa" as Lexer

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Types
Note: ============================================================================

Constant AST_SCRIPT as Integer is 1                     Note: Top-level script
Constant AST_COMMAND as Integer is 2                    Note: Simple command/cmdlet
Constant AST_PIPELINE as Integer is 3                   Note: Pipeline (cmd1 | cmd2)
Constant AST_STATEMENT_LIST as Integer is 4             Note: Statement list (; separated)
Constant AST_BLOCK as Integer is 5                      Note: { statements }

Note: Control Structures
Constant AST_IF_STATEMENT as Integer is 10              Note: if-elseif-else
Constant AST_WHILE_STATEMENT as Integer is 11           Note: while loop
Constant AST_FOR_STATEMENT as Integer is 12             Note: for loop
Constant AST_FOREACH_STATEMENT as Integer is 13         Note: foreach loop
Constant AST_SWITCH_STATEMENT as Integer is 14          Note: switch statement
Constant AST_DO_WHILE as Integer is 15                  Note: do-while loop
Constant AST_DO_UNTIL as Integer is 16                  Note: do-until loop

Note: Function and Class Definitions
Constant AST_FUNCTION_DEFINITION as Integer is 20       Note: function definition
Constant AST_FILTER_DEFINITION as Integer is 21         Note: filter definition
Constant AST_WORKFLOW_DEFINITION as Integer is 22       Note: workflow definition
Constant AST_CLASS_DEFINITION as Integer is 23          Note: class definition
Constant AST_ENUM_DEFINITION as Integer is 24           Note: enum definition
Constant AST_METHOD_DEFINITION as Integer is 25         Note: method definition
Constant AST_PROPERTY_DEFINITION as Integer is 26       Note: property definition

Note: Parameters and Variables
Constant AST_PARAM_BLOCK as Integer is 30               Note: param() block
Constant AST_PARAMETER as Integer is 31                 Note: Parameter declaration
Constant AST_VARIABLE as Integer is 32                  Note: $variable
Constant AST_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT as Integer is 33       Note: $var = value
Constant AST_PROPERTY_ACCESS as Integer is 34           Note: $obj.property
Constant AST_METHOD_CALL as Integer is 35               Note: $obj.method()
Constant AST_ARRAY_ACCESS as Integer is 36              Note: $array[index]

Note: Expressions
Constant AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 40         Note: Binary operation
Constant AST_UNARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 41          Note: Unary operation
Constant AST_SUBEXPRESSION as Integer is 42             Note: $()
Constant AST_ARRAY_SUBEXPRESSION as Integer is 43       Note: @()
Constant AST_HASHTABLE as Integer is 44                 Note: @{}
Constant AST_ARRAY_LITERAL as Integer is 45             Note: @(1,2,3)
Constant AST_TYPE_EXPRESSION as Integer is 46           Note: [type]

Note: Exception Handling
Constant AST_TRY_STATEMENT as Integer is 50             Note: try block
Constant AST_CATCH_STATEMENT as Integer is 51           Note: catch block
Constant AST_FINALLY_STATEMENT as Integer is 52         Note: finally block
Constant AST_THROW_STATEMENT as Integer is 53           Note: throw statement

Note: Flow Control
Constant AST_RETURN_STATEMENT as Integer is 60          Note: return statement
Constant AST_BREAK_STATEMENT as Integer is 61           Note: break statement
Constant AST_CONTINUE_STATEMENT as Integer is 62        Note: continue statement
Constant AST_EXIT_STATEMENT as Integer is 63            Note: exit statement

Note: Literals and Identifiers
Constant AST_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 70                Note: Simple identifier
Constant AST_CMDLET as Integer is 71                    Note: Cmdlet name
Constant AST_STRING_LITERAL as Integer is 72            Note: String literal
Constant AST_NUMBER_LITERAL as Integer is 73            Note: Numeric literal
Constant AST_BOOLEAN_LITERAL as Integer is 74           Note: Boolean literal
Constant AST_NULL_LITERAL as Integer is 75              Note: $null literal

Note: Special Constructs
Constant AST_SWITCH_CLAUSE as Integer is 80             Note: Switch case clause
Constant AST_CASE_LABEL as Integer is 81                Note: Case label
Constant AST_DEFAULT_CLAUSE as Integer is 82            Note: Default clause
Constant AST_REDIRECTION as Integer is 83               Note: Output redirection
Constant AST_COMMENT as Integer is 84                   Note: Comment

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser State Structure
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Parser state layout:
Note: Offset 0: lexer (lexer pointer)
Note: Offset 8: current_token (current token index)
Note: Offset 16: tokens (token array pointer)
Note: Offset 24: token_count (number of tokens)
Note: Offset 32: has_error (error flag)

Process called "create_parser" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create new PowerShell parser

    @Reasoning:
    Initialize parser state with lexer and token stream.
    Set up current position and error tracking.
    @End Reasoning

    Let parser be proc arena_alloc from Layout with 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer

    Let tokens be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 40
    Let token_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 48

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, 0      Note: current_token
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, tokens
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, token_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 0     Note: has_error

    Return parser
End Process

Process called "current_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token type

    Let current_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Let token_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 24

    If current_index is greater than or equal to token_count:
        Return TOKEN_EOF from Lexer
    End If

    Let tokens be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
    Let token_offset be current_index times 24
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with tokens plus token_offset, 0
End Process

Process called "advance_token" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    Let current_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, current_index plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "expect_token" takes parser as Integer, expected as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Expect specific token type and advance

    Let current_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If current_type is equal to expected:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Set error flag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 1
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "match_token" takes parser as Integer, expected as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if current token matches expected type

    Let current_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    Return current_type is equal to expected
End Process

Process called "create_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create new AST node with type

    @Reasoning:
    AST nodes have a standard layout:
    - Type at offset 0
    - Parent at offset 8
    - Children array at offset 16
    - Child count at offset 24
    - Data pointer at offset 32
    @End Reasoning

    Let node be proc arena_alloc from Layout with 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, 0         Note: parent
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0        Note: children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0        Note: child_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0        Note: data

    Return node
End Process

Process called "add_child" takes parent as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add child node to parent

    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 24
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 16

    If children is equal to 0:
        Set children to proc arena_alloc from Layout with 8 times 10  Note: space for 10 children
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 16, children
    End If

    Let child_offset be child_count times 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with children plus child_offset, 0, child
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 24, child_count plus 1

    Note: Set parent pointer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with child, 8, parent

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "skip_newlines" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Skip newline tokens

    While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "parse_script" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse top-level PowerShell script

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell script consists of statements separated by newlines or semicolons.
    Handle empty scripts and optional trailing separators.
    @End Reasoning

    Let script be proc create_ast_node from AST_SCRIPT

    proc skip_newlines from parser

    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
        Let stmt be proc parse_statement from parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from script, stmt
        End If

        Note: Skip statement separators
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer:
                proc advance_token from parser
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
                    proc advance_token from parser
                Otherwise:
                    If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                        If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End While

    Return script
End Process

Process called "parse_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse PowerShell statement

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell statements can be:
    - Control structures (if, while, for, foreach, switch)
    - Function/class definitions
    - Try-catch blocks
    - Simple commands or pipelines
    - Variable assignments
    @End Reasoning

    proc skip_newlines from parser
    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    Note: Control structures
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_if_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_while_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_for_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOREACH from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_foreach_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_switch_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DO from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_do_statement from parser
    End If

    Note: Function and class definitions
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FUNCTION from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_function_definition from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FILTER from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_filter_definition from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WORKFLOW from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_workflow_definition from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_class_definition from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_enum_definition from parser
    End If

    Note: Exception handling
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TRY from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_try_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_THROW from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_throw_statement from parser
    End If

    Note: Flow control
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_return_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BREAK from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_break_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONTINUE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_continue_statement from parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXIT from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_exit_statement from parser
    End If

    Note: Parameter block
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PARAM from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_param_block from parser
    End If

    Note: Comments
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_COMMENT from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_BLOCK_COMMENT from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return proc create_ast_node from AST_COMMENT
    End If

    Note: Default: try to parse as pipeline or command
    Return proc parse_pipeline from parser
End Process

Process called "parse_if_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse if-elseif-else statement

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell if statement syntax:
    if (condition) { statements }
    elseif (condition) { statements }
    else { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let if_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_IF_STATEMENT

    Note: Parse 'if'
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_IF from Lexer

    Note: Parse condition (with or without parentheses)
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    Let condition be proc parse_expression from parser
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from if_stmt, condition
    End If
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Parse if body
    Let if_body be proc parse_block from parser
    If if_body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from if_stmt, if_body
    End If

    Note: Parse elseif clauses
    While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ELSEIF from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser

        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
        Let elseif_condition be proc parse_expression from parser
        If elseif_condition is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from if_stmt, elseif_condition
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

        Let elseif_body be proc parse_block from parser
        If elseif_body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from if_stmt, elseif_body
        End If
    End While

    Note: Parse else clause
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ELSE from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let else_body be proc parse_block from parser
        If else_body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from if_stmt, else_body
        End If
    End If

    Return if_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_while_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse while loop

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell while loop syntax:
    while (condition) { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let while_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_WHILE_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    Let condition be proc parse_expression from parser
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from while_stmt, condition
    End If
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from while_stmt, body
    End If

    Return while_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_for_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse for loop

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell for loop syntax:
    for ($i = 0; $i -lt 10; $i++) { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let for_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_FOR_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_FOR from Lexer

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Parse initialization
    Let init be proc parse_expression from parser
    If init is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from for_stmt, init
    End If
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Note: Parse condition
    Let condition be proc parse_expression from parser
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from for_stmt, condition
    End If
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Note: Parse increment
    Let increment be proc parse_expression from parser
    If increment is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from for_stmt, increment
    End If

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from for_stmt, body
    End If

    Return for_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_foreach_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse foreach loop

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell foreach loop syntax:
    foreach ($item in $collection) { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let foreach_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_FOREACH_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_FOREACH from Lexer

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Parse loop variable
    Let loop_var be proc parse_expression from parser
    If loop_var is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from foreach_stmt, loop_var
    End If

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_IN from Lexer

    Note: Parse collection
    Let collection be proc parse_expression from parser
    If collection is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from foreach_stmt, collection
    End If

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from foreach_stmt, body
    End If

    Return foreach_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_switch_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse switch statement

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell switch statement syntax:
    switch ($expression) {
        value1 { statements }
        value2 { statements }
        default { statements }
    }
    @End Reasoning

    Let switch_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_SWITCH_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    Let expression be proc parse_expression from parser
    If expression is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from switch_stmt, expression
    End If
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    proc skip_newlines from parser

    Note: Parse switch clauses
    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
        Let clause be proc parse_switch_clause from parser
        If clause is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from switch_stmt, clause
        End If
        proc skip_newlines from parser
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return switch_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_switch_clause" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse switch case clause

    Let clause be proc create_ast_node from AST_SWITCH_CLAUSE

    Note: Check for default case
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Note: Check if this is the 'default' keyword
        Let tokens be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16
        Let current_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
        Let token_offset be current_index times 24
        Let token_ptr be tokens plus token_offset
        Let token_text_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token_ptr, 8

        Note: Check if identifier is "default"
        Let is_default be proc string_equals from String with token_text_ptr, "default"

        If is_default is equal to 1:
            Note: This is a default case, create DEFAULT node
            Let default_node be proc create_node from parser, 20201  Note: NODE_DEFAULT
            proc add_child from clause, default_node
            proc advance from parser
        Otherwise:
            Note: Regular case value expression
            Let case_value be proc parse_expression from parser
            If case_value is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from clause, case_value
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Otherwise:
        Note: Regular case value
        Let case_value be proc parse_expression from parser
        If case_value is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from clause, case_value
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse case body
    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from clause, body
    End If

    Return clause
End Process

Process called "parse_do_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse do-while or do-until statement

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell do statement syntax:
    do { statements } while (condition)
    do { statements } until (condition)
    @End Reasoning

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_DO from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_block from parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer:
        Let do_while be proc create_ast_node from AST_DO_WHILE
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from do_while, body
        End If

        proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip 'while'
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
        Let condition be proc parse_expression from parser
        If condition is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from do_while, condition
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

        Return do_while
    End If

    Otherwise:
        Note: Assume do-until
        Let do_until be proc create_ast_node from AST_DO_UNTIL
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from do_until, body
        End If

        Note: Skip optional 'until' keyword
        If proc current_token_type from parser is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
        End If

        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
        Let condition be proc parse_expression from parser
        If condition is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from do_until, condition
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

        Return do_until
    End If
End Process

Process called "parse_function_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse function definition

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell function syntax:
    function Name { param() statements }
    function Name ($param1, $param2) { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let func_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_FUNCTION_DEFINITION

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_FUNCTION from Lexer

    Note: Parse function name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from func_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse optional parameter list
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let param_list be proc parse_parameter_list from parser
        If param_list is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from func_def, param_list
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    End If

    Note: Parse function body
    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from func_def, body
    End If

    Return func_def
End Process

Process called "parse_filter_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse filter definition

    Let filter_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_FILTER_DEFINITION

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_FILTER from Lexer

    Note: Parse filter name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from filter_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse filter body
    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from filter_def, body
    End If

    Return filter_def
End Process

Process called "parse_workflow_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse workflow definition

    Let workflow_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_WORKFLOW_DEFINITION

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_WORKFLOW from Lexer

    Note: Parse workflow name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from workflow_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse workflow body
    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from workflow_def, body
    End If

    Return workflow_def
End Process

Process called "parse_class_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class definition

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell class syntax:
    class ClassName {
        [type] $property
        ClassName($param) { }
        [type] Method($param) { }
    }
    @End Reasoning

    Let class_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_CLASS_DEFINITION

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer

    Note: Parse class name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from class_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse class body
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    proc skip_newlines from parser

    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
        Let member be proc parse_class_member from parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from class_def, member
        End If
        proc skip_newlines from parser
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return class_def
End Process

Process called "parse_class_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class member (property or method)

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    Note: Check for type annotation
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        Note: Type annotation - could be property or method
        Return proc parse_typed_member from parser
    End If

    Note: Check for constructor (class name)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Note: Could be constructor or method
        Return proc parse_method_or_constructor from parser
    End If

    Note: Variable assignment (property)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VARIABLE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_property_definition from parser
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_typed_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse typed member (with [type] annotation)

    Note: Parse type annotation
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer
    Let type_expr be proc parse_type_expression from parser
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VARIABLE from Lexer:
        Note: Typed property
        Let prop_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_PROPERTY_DEFINITION
        If type_expr is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from prop_def, type_expr
        End If

        Let var_node be proc parse_variable from parser
        If var_node is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from prop_def, var_node
        End If

        Return prop_def
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Note: Typed method
        Let method_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_METHOD_DEFINITION
        If type_expr is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from method_def, type_expr
        End If

        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from method_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser

        Note: Parse parameter list
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Let param_list be proc parse_parameter_list from parser
            If param_list is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from method_def, param_list
            End If
            proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        End If

        Note: Parse method body
        Let body be proc parse_block from parser
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from method_def, body
        End If

        Return method_def
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_method_or_constructor" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse method or constructor

    Let method_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_METHOD_DEFINITION

    Note: Parse method name
    Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc add_child from method_def, name_node
    proc advance_token from parser

    Note: Parse parameter list
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let param_list be proc parse_parameter_list from parser
        If param_list is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from method_def, param_list
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    End If

    Note: Parse method body
    Let body be proc parse_block from parser
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from method_def, body
    End If

    Return method_def
End Process

Process called "parse_property_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse property definition

    Let prop_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_PROPERTY_DEFINITION

    Let var_node be proc parse_variable from parser
    If var_node is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from prop_def, var_node
    End If

    Note: Parse optional assignment
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let value be proc parse_expression from parser
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from prop_def, value
        End If
    End If

    Return prop_def
End Process

Process called "parse_enum_definition" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse enum definition

    Let enum_def be proc create_ast_node from AST_ENUM_DEFINITION

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer

    Note: Parse enum name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let name_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from enum_def, name_node
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse enum body
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    proc skip_newlines from parser

    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
        Note: Parse enum member
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
            Let member_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
            proc add_child from enum_def, member_node
            proc advance_token from parser

            Note: Parse optional value assignment
            If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer is equal to 1:
                proc advance_token from parser
                Let value be proc parse_expression from parser
                If value is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_child from member_node, value
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Skip optional comma
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
        End If

        proc skip_newlines from parser
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return enum_def
End Process

Process called "parse_try_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse try-catch-finally statement

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell try statement syntax:
    try { statements }
    catch [ExceptionType] { statements }
    finally { statements }
    @End Reasoning

    Let try_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_TRY_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_TRY from Lexer

    Note: Parse try body
    Let try_body be proc parse_block from parser
    If try_body is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child from try_stmt, try_body
    End If

    Note: Parse catch blocks
    While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_CATCH from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser

        Let catch_block be proc create_ast_node from AST_CATCH_STATEMENT

        Note: Parse optional exception type
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Let exception_type be proc parse_type_expression from parser
            If exception_type is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from catch_block, exception_type
            End If
            proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer
        End If

        Note: Parse catch body
        Let catch_body be proc parse_block from parser
        If catch_body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from catch_block, catch_body
        End If

        proc add_child from try_stmt, catch_block
    End While

    Note: Parse finally block
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_FINALLY from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser

        Let finally_block be proc create_ast_node from AST_FINALLY_STATEMENT
        Let finally_body be proc parse_block from parser
        If finally_body is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from finally_block, finally_body
        End If

        proc add_child from try_stmt, finally_block
    End If

    Return try_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_throw_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse throw statement

    Let throw_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_THROW_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_THROW from Lexer

    Note: Parse optional expression
    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer and token_type is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Let expression be proc parse_expression from parser
        If expression is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from throw_stmt, expression
        End If
    End If

    Return throw_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_return_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse return statement

    Let return_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_RETURN_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer

    Note: Parse optional expression
    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer and token_type is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Let expression be proc parse_expression from parser
        If expression is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from return_stmt, expression
        End If
    End If

    Return return_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_break_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse break statement

    Let break_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_BREAK_STATEMENT
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_BREAK from Lexer
    Return break_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_continue_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse continue statement

    Let continue_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_CONTINUE_STATEMENT
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_CONTINUE from Lexer
    Return continue_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_exit_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse exit statement

    Let exit_stmt be proc create_ast_node from AST_EXIT_STATEMENT

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_EXIT from Lexer

    Note: Parse optional exit code
    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NUMBER from Lexer:
        Let exit_code be proc parse_expression from parser
        If exit_code is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from exit_stmt, exit_code
        End If
    End If

    Return exit_stmt
End Process

Process called "parse_param_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse param() block

    Let param_block be proc create_ast_node from AST_PARAM_BLOCK

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_PARAM from Lexer
    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Parse parameter list
    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
        Let param be proc parse_parameter_declaration from parser
        If param is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from param_block, param
        End If

        Note: Skip optional comma
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Return param_block
End Process

Process called "parse_parameter_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse parameter declaration

    Let param_decl be proc create_ast_node from AST_PARAMETER

    Note: Parse optional type annotation
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let type_expr be proc parse_type_expression from parser
        If type_expr is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from param_decl, type_expr
        End If
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer
    End If

    Note: Parse parameter variable
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_VARIABLE from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let var_node be proc parse_variable from parser
        If var_node is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from param_decl, var_node
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse optional default value
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let default_value be proc parse_expression from parser
        If default_value is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from param_decl, default_value
        End If
    End If

    Return param_decl
End Process

Process called "parse_parameter_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse comma-separated parameter list

    Let param_list be proc create_ast_node from AST_PARAM_BLOCK

    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
        Let param be proc parse_parameter_declaration from parser
        If param is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from param_list, param
        End If

        Note: Skip optional comma
        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
        End If
    End While

    Return param_list
End Process

Process called "parse_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse statement block { statements }

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell blocks are enclosed in braces and contain statements.
    Statements are separated by newlines or semicolons.
    @End Reasoning

    Let block be proc create_ast_node from AST_BLOCK

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    proc skip_newlines from parser

    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
        Let stmt be proc parse_statement from parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from block, stmt
        End If

        Note: Skip statement separators
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer:
                proc advance_token from parser
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
                    proc advance_token from parser
                Otherwise:
                    If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                        If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return block
End Process

Process called "parse_pipeline" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse pipeline (command | command | ...)

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell pipelines connect commands with | operator.
    Each stage can be a simple command or complex expression.
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_command from parser

    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let pipeline be proc create_ast_node from AST_PIPELINE

        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from pipeline, left
        End If

        While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer is equal to 1:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Let right be proc parse_command from parser
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from pipeline, right
            End If
        End While

        Return pipeline
    End If

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_command" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse command or cmdlet invocation

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell commands can be:
    - Cmdlets (Get-Process, Write-Host)
    - Functions
    - Expressions with assignments
    - Method calls
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    Note: Check for variable assignment
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VARIABLE from Lexer:
        Note: Might be assignment or just variable reference
        Let saved_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
        Let var_node be proc parse_variable from parser

        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer is equal to 1:
            Note: Variable assignment
            Let assignment be proc create_ast_node from AST_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT
            If var_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from assignment, var_node
            End If

            proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip =
            Let value be proc parse_expression from parser
            If value is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from assignment, value
            End If

            Return assignment
        End If

        Otherwise:
            Note: Just variable reference - reset and parse as expression
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, saved_pos
            Return proc parse_expression from parser
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse as expression (includes cmdlets, method calls, etc.)
    Return proc parse_expression from parser
End Process

Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse PowerShell expression

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell expressions include:
    - Variables and literals
    - Method calls and property access
    - Arithmetic and logical operations
    - Cmdlet invocations
    - Array and hashtable literals
    - Subexpressions
    @End Reasoning

    Return proc parse_logical_or_expression from parser
End Process

Process called "parse_logical_or_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse logical OR expression

    Let left be proc parse_logical_and_expression from parser

    While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_OR from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let or_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from or_expr, left
        End If

        proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip -or
        Let right be proc parse_logical_and_expression from parser
        If right is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from or_expr, right
        End If

        Set left to or_expr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_logical_and_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse logical AND expression

    Let left be proc parse_equality_expression from parser

    While proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_AND from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let and_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from and_expr, left
        End If

        proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip -and
        Let right be proc parse_equality_expression from parser
        If right is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from and_expr, right
        End If

        Set left to and_expr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_equality_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse equality expression (-eq, -ne)

    Let left be proc parse_relational_expression from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EQ from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_NE from Lexer:
            Let eq_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from eq_expr, left
            End If

            proc advance_token from parser
            Let right be proc parse_relational_expression from parser
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from eq_expr, right
            End If

            Set left to eq_expr
        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_relational_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse relational expression (-gt, -ge, -lt, -le)

    Let left be proc parse_additive_expression from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GT from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_GE from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_LT from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_LE from Lexer:
            Let rel_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from rel_expr, left
            End If

            proc advance_token from parser
            Let right be proc parse_additive_expression from parser
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from rel_expr, right
            End If

            Set left to rel_expr
        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_additive_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse additive expression (+, -)

    Let left be proc parse_multiplicative_expression from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
            Let add_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from add_expr, left
            End If

            proc advance_token from parser
            Let right be proc parse_multiplicative_expression from parser
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from add_expr, right
            End If

            Set left to add_expr
        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_multiplicative_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse multiplicative expression (*, /, %)

    Let left be proc parse_unary_expression from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MULTIPLY from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_DIVIDE from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_MODULO from Lexer:
            Let mul_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from mul_expr, left
            End If

            proc advance_token from parser
            Let right be proc parse_unary_expression from parser
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from mul_expr, right
            End If

            Set left to mul_expr
        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_unary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse unary expression (-not, !, +, -)

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NOT from Lexer:
        Let unary_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_UNARY_EXPRESSION
        proc advance_token from parser

        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression from parser
        If operand is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from unary_expr, operand
        End If

        Return unary_expr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
        Let unary_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_UNARY_EXPRESSION
        proc advance_token from parser

        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression from parser
        If operand is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from unary_expr, operand
        End If

        Return unary_expr
    End If

    Return proc parse_postfix_expression from parser
End Process

Process called "parse_postfix_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse postfix expression (property access, method calls, array indexing)

    Let left be proc parse_primary_expression from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DOT from Lexer:
            Note: Property access or method call
            proc advance_token from parser

            Let member_name be proc current_token_type from parser
            If member_name is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
                proc advance_token from parser

                Note: Check if method call
                If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer is equal to 1:
                    Let method_call be proc create_ast_node from AST_METHOD_CALL
                    If left is not equal to 0:
                        proc add_child from method_call, left
                    End If

                    proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip (
                    Note: Parse arguments
                    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                        Let arg be proc parse_expression from parser
                        If arg is not equal to 0:
                            proc add_child from method_call, arg
                        End If

                        If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer is equal to 1:
                            proc advance_token from parser
                        End If
                    End While
                    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

                    Set left to method_call
                End If

                Otherwise:
                    Note: Property access
                    Let prop_access be proc create_ast_node from AST_PROPERTY_ACCESS
                    If left is not equal to 0:
                        proc add_child from prop_access, left
                    End If

                    Let prop_name be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
                    proc add_child from prop_access, prop_name

                    Set left to prop_access
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
                Note: Array indexing
                Let array_access be proc create_ast_node from AST_ARRAY_ACCESS
                If left is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_child from array_access, left
                End If

                proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip [
                Let index be proc parse_expression from parser
                If index is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_child from array_access, index
                End If
                proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer

                Set left to array_access
            Otherwise:
                If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                    If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

Process called "parse_primary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse primary expression (literals, variables, parenthesized expressions)

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    Note: Variables
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VARIABLE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_variable from parser
    End If

    Note: Literals
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NUMBER from Lexer:
        Let number_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_NUMBER_LITERAL
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return number_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_EXPANDABLE_STRING from Lexer:
        Let string_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_STRING_LITERAL
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return string_node
    End If

    Note: Identifiers and cmdlets
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let id_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return id_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CMDLET from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_cmdlet_invocation from parser
    End If

    Note: Subexpressions
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SUBEXPR from Lexer:
        Let subexpr be proc create_ast_node from AST_SUBEXPRESSION
        proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip $(

        Let expr be proc parse_expression from parser
        If expr is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from subexpr, expr
        End If

        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        Return subexpr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ARRAY_SUBEXPR from Lexer:
        Let array_subexpr be proc create_ast_node from AST_ARRAY_SUBEXPRESSION
        proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip @(

        Note: Parse array elements
        While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            Let element be proc parse_expression from parser
            If element is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from array_subexpr, element
            End If

            If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer is equal to 1:
                proc advance_token from parser
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        Return array_subexpr
    End If

    Note: Hashtables
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AT_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_hashtable from parser
    End If

    Note: Type expressions
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_type_expression from parser
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized expressions
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let expr be proc parse_expression from parser
        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        Return expr
    End If

    Note: Parameters (when used as arguments)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PARAMETER from Lexer:
        Let param_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_PARAMETER
        proc advance_token from parser

        Note: Parse optional parameter value
        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer and token_type is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer and token_type is not equal to TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer:
            Let value be proc parse_expression from parser
            If value is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child from param_node, value
            End If
        End If

        Return param_node
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "parse_variable" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse PowerShell variable

    Let var_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_VARIABLE
    proc advance_token from parser
    Return var_node
End Process

Process called "parse_cmdlet_invocation" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse cmdlet invocation with parameters

    @Reasoning:
    PowerShell cmdlets can be invoked with named and positional parameters:
    Get-Process -Name notepad
    Write-Host "Hello World" -ForegroundColor Red
    @End Reasoning

    Let cmdlet_node be proc create_ast_node from AST_CMDLET
    proc advance_token from parser

    Note: Parse arguments and parameters
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        Note: Stop at pipeline, newline, or semicolon
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Parse parameter or argument
        Let arg be proc parse_expression from parser
        If arg is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from cmdlet_node, arg
        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:  Note: break if no argument
                If 1 is not equal to 1:  Note: force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return cmdlet_node
End Process

Process called "parse_hashtable" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse hashtable literal @{ key = value; ... }

    Let hashtable be proc create_ast_node from AST_HASHTABLE

    proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip @{

    proc skip_newlines from parser

    Note: Parse key-value pairs
    While proc current_token_type from parser is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
        Note: Parse key
        Let key be proc parse_expression from parser
        If key is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from hashtable, key
        End If

        proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer

        Note: Parse value
        Let value be proc parse_expression from parser
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child from hashtable, value
        End If

        Note: Skip optional separator
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            proc skip_newlines from parser
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return hashtable
End Process

Process called "parse_type_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type expression [Type]

    Let type_expr be proc create_ast_node from AST_TYPE_EXPRESSION

    proc advance_token from parser  Note: skip [

    Note: Parse type name
    If proc match_token from parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer is equal to 1:
        Let type_name be proc create_ast_node from AST_IDENTIFIER
        proc add_child from type_expr, type_name
        proc advance_token from parser
    End If

    proc expect_token from parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer

    Return type_expr
End Process

Process called "parse" takes source as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for PowerShell parsing

    @Reasoning:
    Complete PowerShell parsing pipeline:
    1. Tokenize source code
    2. Create parser with token stream
    3. Parse script into AST
    4. Return AST root node
    @End Reasoning

    Let lexer be proc tokenize from Lexer with source, length
    Let parser be proc create_parser from lexer
    Return proc parse_script from parser
End Process